name: Artistic Childhood White Frame
description:
Every day, she comes into the store… Every day, she walks straight to the spray paints and picks up two cans… Every day, she doesn’t say a word and just hands you the cans and her money and only says “thank you” and carefully walks out of the store, as if she’s avoiding someone?

Something about her is odd as well, she always comes in with that blue bow and a very expensive looking dress and her hair, even if it’s curly, is always stylized in a way where it looks like she spends at least an hour each day styling it. I have no idea who she is or where she came from, she just suddenly popped up one day and became our number one customer who we don’t even know her name.


My manager tells me never to ask questions to our customers but I really gotta ask her why she keeps coming back here or what exactly she’s doing with those cans of spray paint, but she’s been doing it every day for the past year and a half now. We also don’t live in any major city where graffiti is an issue, no we live in a cozy little suburb… so… what on earth is she buying all of our spray paint for?

—-

The Gallery Gehenna Project is a daily art project where there are multiple frames for each individual artwork, each with different types of rarity applied. White frames are initially only given out via giveaways. All artworks will be compatible within the Gallery Gehenna Game with each artwork unlocking a playable story segment.
